<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-09-04T18:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-09-04T18:36:00-05:00" n="1131" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1131">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.6363/246</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Parker</persName>,
                                representing American interests, to the <gloss type="to">Secretary
                                    of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico City</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-09-04T17:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">September 4, 1916, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>374. Department of Hacienda to-day publishes a decree dated September 2
                            requiring all oil compaines producing crude oil in Mexico to register in
                            the tax bureau of that Department before September 15 for companies
                            already producing and within 15 days from the <pb facs="0849" n="773" xml:id="pg_773"/> date of first production for the companies which
                            have not yet produced oil. This registration must be made by a person
                            duly authorized to represent the company. Failure to comply may be
                            punished by a fine of one thousand pesos Mexican gold.</p>
                        <p>Text and translation will be sent by first pouch.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Parker</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>